商标；品牌；标志；烙印（尤指农场牲畜身上表示所属的印记）；火印；燃烧的木柴；烧焦的木头；污名；耻辱
标记；给…贴上（不好的）标签；污名化；给…留下深刻印象；给…带来不良影响；打烙印于；给（牲畜）打烙印；识别；区分

0.en: And they built something else as well, a brand.
0.cn: 他们还会建造其他的东西，一个品牌。

1.en: Who you are is your brand, and saying that a brand is simply a name is like saying Abraham Lincoln is simply a name, Or Mahatma Gandhi, God.
1.cn: 而你，就是你的品牌，而说你的品牌，只是个名字，就像在说亚伯拉罕·林肯只是个名字，圣雄甘地，上帝只是个名字。

2.en: It looks like "Eat it, eat it, you losers," might just be your brand.
2.cn: 看来"吃屎吧，废柴们，"可以当你们的品牌名啊。

3.en: But you have political instincts. And you're a brand. You're St. Alicia.
3.cn: 但你有政治直觉，你有品牌效应，你是圣人艾丽西娅。

4.en: Go after the clients I represent. Correct. You're a brand now. Saint Alicia.
4.cn: 从我代理的客户下手。对，你现在是品牌，圣人艾丽西娅。

5.en: It also turned out that people who bought store brand medication didn't feel as well.
5.cn: 研究还发现购买了普通品牌药物的人，同样也感觉治疗效果不好。

6.en: Good. Another part of your brand is that you stood by your husband. Six years ago.
6.cn: 很好，你品牌的另一组成部分，就是你支持你的丈夫，6年前的事了。

7.en: Darling, I hired these people for their expertise, and ultimately, they feel that we would be doing the brand a disservice.
7.cn: 亲爱的，我雇这些人来给我专业意见，最终，他们觉得我们是在为这个品牌帮倒忙。

8.en: As many of you know, recently Massimo Corteleoni has agreed to finance the expansion of the James Holt label transforming the work of this visionary artist into a global brand, which is really an exciting enterprise.
8.cn: 正如大部分人所知最近马西莫·科特利让内决定为詹姆斯·浩特这个品牌注资，将这位富于创造灵感的艺术家的作品转变成一个全球品牌，一个振奋人心的产业。

9.cn: 那你到底是谁？我叫皮特布兰德。

10.en: I wouldn't leave you behind, Dr. Brand.

11.en: You know my father, Professor Brand. We're NASA.
11.cn: 你认识我父亲， Brand教授，我们是NASA的。

14.en: Today, people, we are gonna debut the brand-new Care Bear bikini!
14.cn: 都听好了，今天就是爱心熊比基尼的处女秀！

15.en: It's new every time. It's brand new every night. It's very, very exciting.
15.cn: 每一次都是新的。每晚都是完全不同的。非常，非常地激动人心。

16.en: And I'll tell you that the one thing they understood about this brand-new nation was to stick together, because every direction they turned was brand-new undiscovered country.
16.cn: 我要告诉你们的是对于这个新成立的国家他们认识到最重要的一点就是团结一致，因为他们做的每一个决定都是全新的，前无古人的。

17.en: But her cows produce a lot of waste, and she's found a brand-new way to use it.
17.cn: 但她的奶牛就浪费不少了，她找到了一个新方法加以利用。

18.en: He fed them the science and specs. All so they could build him a brand-new body.
18.cn: 他提供人类技术和规格！好让他们为他打造全新躯壳。

19.en: So who wants to go in the back, and see how amazing our brand-new cupcake shop is?
19.cn: 有谁想去后面看看我们新的蛋糕店?
